09:38.017 --> 09:39.218
No, no, no. Come in, come in.

09:39.286 --> 09:40.353
You sure? Ok.

09:40.420 --> 09:41.187
I just got a little carried

09:41.254 --> 09:41.887
away.

09:41.955 --> 09:42.755
Working out?

09:42.822 --> 09:45.023
Yeah. It's kind of a metaphor

09:45.091 --> 09:46.391
for my life these days.

09:46.459 --> 09:47.292
You want some water?

09:47.359 --> 09:48.326
Oh, no, thanks. I'm good.

09:48.394 --> 09:49.393
I just keep running

09:49.461 --> 09:51.362
and running without a clue

09:51.429 --> 09:52.396
where I'm going.

09:52.463 --> 09:53.796
Well, at least you care about

09:53.864 --> 09:55.664
your health and your body.

09:55.732 --> 09:56.698
Christian's at home laying

09:56.766 --> 09:57.865
on the couch drinking beer

09:57.933 --> 09:59.533
like a fat slob. Seems he's

09:59.601 --> 10:00.567
given up.

10:00.635 --> 10:01.668
Well, maybe that's his way of

10:01.736 --> 10:02.768
saying he's happy.

10:02.836 --> 10:04.737
Or maybe it's his way of

10:04.805 --> 10:05.505
telling me he doesn't care

10:05.572 --> 10:06.972
what I think.

10:07.040 --> 10:09.375
Ah.

10:09.443 --> 10:10.510
Well, he is proud of you,

10:10.578 --> 10:11.444
Kimber.

10:11.512 --> 10:12.979
I suppose.

10:13.046 --> 10:15.547
Well, ok. I hope you like

10:15.614 --> 10:17.382
what I put together.

10:17.450 --> 10:18.283
Do you mind?

10:18.351 --> 10:20.318
No, no. Yeah, yeah.

10:20.385 --> 10:22.386
First one.

